result.execSummary:
The defendant Eric J Duane was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate Firearm While Intoxicated, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Eric J Duane in court with Attorney Thomas Patrick Grieve.  Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court quashes warrant.  Court re-instates signature bond previously ordered forfeited.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Grieve makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $379.00  - to be paid at in 20 days, alternate 8 days jail if not paid.   
 
            **COURT ORDERS DEFENDANT TO FORFEIT FIREARM INVOLVED IN INCIDENT TO THE STATE**
